======================================================================
CROWN JEWEL THEOREMS — FOURIER STRUCTURE OF H
opus-2026-03-14-S89
======================================================================

======================================================================
THEOREM 1: E_2/E_0 = (n-2)/m
======================================================================
  n=3: predicted = 1/3, actual = 1/3, ✓
  n=4: predicted = 1/3, actual = 1/3, ✓
  n=5: predicted = 3/10, actual = 3/10, ✓
  n=6: predicted = 4/15, actual = 4/15, ✓
  n=7: predicted = 5/21, actual = 5/21, ✓

  Proof sketch:
  • Level-2 Fourier coefficient ĉ_{e1,e2} is nonzero iff edges e1,e2 share a vertex
  • Count of adjacent pairs: n × C(n-1, 2) = n(n-1)(n-2)/2
  • Each has magnitude |ĉ| = Mean/m = n!/(2^{n-1} × m)
  • E_2/E_0 = n(n-1)(n-2)/2 × (Mean/m)² / Mean² = (n-2)/m

======================================================================
THEOREM 2: E_{{n-1}}/E_0 = 2/n! for odd n
======================================================================
  n=3: E_{2}/E_0 = 1/3 = 2/3! = 1/3 ✓
  n=5: E_{4}/E_0 = 1/60 = 2/5! = 1/60 ✓
  n=7: E_{6}/E_0 = 1/2520 = 2/7! = 1/2520 ✓

  Proof sketch:
  • At level n-1 (even for odd n), the nonzero subsets are exactly
    the n!/2 Hamiltonian paths of K_n (undirected)
  • Each has |ĉ| = 1/2^{n-2}
  • E_{n-1} = (n!/2) × (1/2^{n-2})² = n!/(2^{2n-3})
  • E_0 = Mean² = (n!/2^{n-1})² = (n!)²/2^{2n-2}
  • E_{n-1}/E_0 = n!/(2^{2n-3}) × 2^{2n-2}/(n!)² = 2/n!

  Predictions for odd n=9:
    E_8/E_0 = 2/9! = 1/181440 = 0.000005511464

======================================================================
THEOREM 3: Only even levels contribute (complement symmetry)
======================================================================
  H(T̄) = H(T) for all tournaments T
  Proof: Complementing T reverses all arcs.
    If v₁→v₂→...→vₙ is a Ham path in T,
    then vₙ→vₙ₋₁→...→v₁ is a Ham path in T̄.
    This bijection preserves count: H(T̄) = H(T).
  
  Walsh coefficient: ĉ_S(f(T̄)) = (-1)^{|S|} ĉ_S(f(T))
  Since f(T̄) = f(T): ĉ_S × ((-1)^{|S|} - 1) = 0
  For |S| odd: ĉ_S = 0  ■

======================================================================
INTERMEDIATE LEVELS: STRUCTURE AND PATTERNS
======================================================================

  Level 4 energies:
    n=5 (m=10): E_4/E_0 = 1/60 = 0.0166666667
    n=6 (m=15): E_4/E_0 = 1/45 = 0.0222222222
    n=7 (m=21): E_4/E_0 = 3/140 = 0.0214285714

  Level 4 coefficient decomposition:
    Type A: Hamiltonian path on 5-vertex subgraph of K_n
      Count = C(n,5) × 60 where 60 = 5!/2
      n=5: 60 subsets
      n=6: 360 subsets
      n=7: 1260 subsets

    Type B: Two disjoint P₃ covering 6-vertex subgraph of K_n
      Count = C(n,6) × 90
      n=6: 90 subsets
      n=7: 630 subsets

    Magnitudes:
      n=5: type A |ĉ| = 1/8
      n=6: type A |ĉ| = 1/8, type B |ĉ| = 1/4
      n=7: type A |ĉ| = 3/16, type B |ĉ| = 3/8

  Verification:
    n=5: E_4 = 60×(1/8)² + 0×(0)² = 15/16
          E_4/E_0 = 1/60 = 1/60 ✓
    n=6: E_4 = 360×(1/8)² + 90×(1/4)² = 45/4
          E_4/E_0 = 1/45 = 1/45 ✓
    n=7: E_4 = 1260×(3/16)² + 630×(3/8)² = 8505/64
          E_4/E_0 = 3/140 = 3/140 ✓

  Magnitude scaling factor for type A (Ham path of K₅):
    n=5→6: 1/8 → 1/8 (factor = 1)
    n=6→7: 1/8 → 3/16 (factor = 3/2)
    Pattern: |ĉ_A|(n) = (n-4)/2^{n-2}?
      n=5: (n-4)/2^{n-2} = 1/8, actual = 1/8 ✓
      n=6: (n-4)/2^{n-2} = 1/8, actual = 1/8 ✓
      n=7: (n-4)/2^{n-2} = 3/32, actual = 3/16 ✗

  Magnitude for type B (double P₃):
    n=6: |ĉ_B| = 1/4 = 2 × 1/8
    n=7: |ĉ_B| = 3/8 = 2 × 3/16
    Pattern: |ĉ_B| = 2 × |ĉ_A| always!
      n=6: 2×|ĉ_A| = 1/4, |ĉ_B| = 1/4, match = True
      n=7: 2×|ĉ_A| = 3/8, |ĉ_B| = 3/8, match = True

======================================================================
GRAND VARIANCE FORMULA
======================================================================

  Var/Mean² = Σ_{k=1}^{floor((n-1)/2)} E_{2k}/E_0
  where:
    E_2/E_0 = (n-2)/m = 2(n-2)/(n(n-1))
    E_{n-1}/E_0 = 2/n!  (for odd n)
    
  Var/Mean² denominators:
    n=3: Var/Mean² = 1/3, denom = 3
    n=4: Var/Mean² = 1/3, denom = 3
    n=5: Var/Mean² = 19/60, denom = 60
    n=6: Var/Mean² = 13/45, denom = 45
    n=7: Var/Mean² = 131/504, denom = 504

  Denominator factorizations:
    n=3: 3 = 3
    n=4: 3 = 3
    n=5: 60 = 2² × 3 × 5 = 5!/2
    n=6: 45 = 3² × 5
    n=7: 504 = 2³ × 3² × 7 = 7!/10

  LCD structure:
    n=5: level denoms = [10, 60], LCD = 60
           Var/Mean² = 19/60 = 19/60
    n=6: level denoms = [15, 45], LCD = 45
           Var/Mean² = 13/45 = 13/45
    n=7: level denoms = [21, 140, 2520], LCD = 2520
           Var/Mean² = 131/504 = 131/504

